---
// Fundations
import Text from "@/components/fundations/elements/Text.astro";
import Wrapper from "@/components/fundations/containers/Wrapper.astro";
---

<section>
  <Wrapper variant="standard" class="py-12">
    <Text
      tag="h3"
      variant="textLG"
      class="dark:text-white text-base-900 text-balance"
    >
      Overview
    </Text>
    <div
      class="grid items-start grid-cols-1 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mt-1 pt-4 relative before:absolute after:absolute before:bg-black after:bg-base-200 dark:before:bg-base-50 dark:after:bg-base-50/10 before:top-0 before:left-0 before:h-px before:w-18 after:top-0 after:right-0 after:left-20 after:h-px"
    >
      <Text
        tag="p"
        variant="textBase"
        class="text-base-500 dark:text-base-300 lg:text-balance"
      >
        In todayâ€™s fast-paced market, great design is the key to creating
        products that stand out. Mastering Product Design: From Concept to
        Creation is a comprehensive course that equips you with the skills to
        design innovative, user-centered products. Whether you're a beginner or
        an experienced designer looking to refine your craft, this course covers
        everything from design thinking and prototyping to usability testing and
        market validation.
        <br />
        <br />
        Through hands-on projects, real-world case studies, and expert insights,
        you'll learn how to transform ideas into functional, aesthetically pleasing,
        and market-ready products. By the end of this course, you'll have the knowledge
        and confidence to create compelling designs that solve real problems and
        drive business success.
      </Text>

      <div class="p-8 bg-base-100 dark:bg-base-900">
        <Text tag="h3" variant="textBase" class="dark:text-white text-base-900">
          Course details
        </Text>

        <Wrapper variant="prose" class="mt-2">
          <ul class="text-xs" role="list">
            <li>
              <span>Duration:</span> 8 weeks (Self-paced or Instructor-led)
            </li>
            <li><span>Level:</span> Beginner to Intermediate</li>
            <li>
              <span>Format:</span> Online with video lectures, assignments, and hands-on
              projects
            </li>
            <li>
              <span>Tools Covered:</span> Figma, Sketch, Adobe XD, Prototyping Tools
            </li>
            <li>
              <span>Key Topics:</span>
              <ul>
                <li>Introduction to Product Design & Design Thinking</li>
                <li>Understanding User Needs & Market Research</li>
                <li>Wireframing, Prototyping, and Usability Testing</li>
                <li>Visual & Interaction Design Principles</li>
                <li>Collaboration with Developers and Stakeholders</li>
                <li>Designing for Accessibility and Inclusivity</li>
                <li>Final Project: Designing a Real-World Product</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span>Certificate:</span> Yes, upon successful completion
            </li>
            <li>
              <span>Who Should Enroll?</span> UX/UI designers, product managers,
              developers, entrepreneurs, or anyone interested in product design.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </Wrapper>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Wrapper>
</section>
